1
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:41,200
(Touch Your Heart)

2
00:00:41,866 --> 00:00:43,733
(Episode 10)

3
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,000
Huh? Kwon!

4
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,686
Just when I thought
you were over it,

5
00:00:55,766 --> 00:00:56,853
here you are again,
waiting for me...

6
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:59,153
What, you think
I've been waiting for you?

7
00:00:59,233 --> 00:01:01,666
Yes I have, in fact.
For four and a half hours!

8
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,653
Hey, you think I really would?

9
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,786
Why would I wait for you?

10
00:01:05,866 --> 00:01:07,600
If you were Yoon-seo, sure.

11
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:11,533
Oh my gosh!

12
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,100
Yoon-seo...

13
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:15,633
I mean, Yun-sook.

14
00:01:36,433 --> 00:01:38,353
They're an office couple!

15
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,186
I caught them a few times,

16
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:41,866
holding hands on the rooftop.

17
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,200
I see. No wonder...

18
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:50,453
Good times!
Holding hands in secret,

19
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:52,786
meeting up secretly
on the rooftop...

20
00:01:52,866 --> 00:01:54,166
It must be so good.

21
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:57,453
If you're that envious of them,
why don't you try it, too?

22
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:58,533
What...

23
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:01,400
Aren't you married?

24
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:08,286
It's been a while
since I saw that smile.

25
00:02:08,366 --> 00:02:09,366
Yes, well...

26
00:02:11,566 --> 00:02:13,720
I ought to have been taken early
with these looks,

27
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,100
but I'm still single, in fact.

28
00:02:17,233 --> 00:02:19,186
In my thirties,
I was too busy with

29
00:02:19,266 --> 00:02:21,886
defending justice on the
side of the powerless,

30
00:02:21,966 --> 00:02:25,320
and in my forties,
I jumped into management

31
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:29,000
working around the clock,
so I'm still single...

32
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,586
I see.

33
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:34,820
But you've still got it,
so do find someone.

34
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,853
I say go for
someone in the office.

35
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:41,586
Like you said, it sounds
quite romantic and thrilling.

36
00:02:41,666 --> 00:02:43,153
Office dating?

37
00:02:43,233 --> 00:02:44,366
But with who?

38
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,733
Good morning!

39
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,720
- Ah, you're here.
- Good morning!

40
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,086
Have some waffles.
Mr. Choi bought them for us.

41
00:02:53,166 --> 00:02:56,120
Ah, that's great.
I haven't had breakfast.

42
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,720
Yum! I love waffles.

43
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,253
Go on and sit.

44
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,333
Come on, sit.

45
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:09,166
But why waffles, all of a sudden?

46
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:12,153
I just suddenly remembered that

47
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,286
winter in Canada.

48
00:03:14,366 --> 00:03:19,253
The snowy fields of Canada were
as cold as her heart,

49
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,920
and the only thing that
warmed me up then,

50
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,366
were these waffles topped with
maple syrup.

51
00:03:27,466 --> 00:03:28,320
So, how is it?

52
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,800
- Good.
- Right? It's delicious.

53
00:03:31,266 --> 00:03:32,266
- Right?
- Yes.

54
00:03:33,066 --> 00:03:34,066
The syrup?

55
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,266
It's good.

56
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:47,500
Yoon-seo.

57
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,200
Why...

58
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:51,266
Why are you doing this?

59
00:03:54,266 --> 00:03:55,253
Is there something in your eye?

60
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:57,220
- Yes.
- Oh, so you do!

61
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,220
There's something in your eye.

62
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,220
- Saline solution!
- There's something there.

63
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,520
- Something big!
- Saline solution!

64
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,453
I have it in my room,
I always keep some on me.

65
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:03,453
Do you want me to take a look?

66
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:04,733
No, it's alright.

67
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,153
Oh, come on!

68
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,320
Don't just start winking

69
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,286
when everyone is there!

70
00:04:21,366 --> 00:04:23,153
But back in the elevator,

71
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:25,186
you said office dating was
romantic and full of thrills

72
00:04:25,266 --> 00:04:28,153
because of all the
secret exchanges.

73
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,453
Oh what? Still...

74
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:33,133
If you do that
without a warning...

75
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:35,266
You just totally got me!

76
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,753
Actually, you know what?

77
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:44,286
We should make use of
what time we have remaining.

78
00:04:44,366 --> 00:04:45,820
So we don't regret it.

79
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:48,033
I'll do my best to
help you in that field.

80
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,400
Mmm, good!

81
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:58,120
Now that I think about it,

82
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:00,200
it's my first time
having lunch with you.

83
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:02,986
Yes, restaurants tend to get

84
00:05:03,066 --> 00:05:05,420
crowded during lunchtime,

85
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,286
and I find that
a little uncomfortable, so...

86
00:05:07,366 --> 00:05:10,200
Oh, right. I guess you want to
avoid crowded places.

87
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:13,120
I hope I wasn't forcing you to
join me today, then.

88
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:17,333
No, no. Closed rooms like
this one are fine.

89
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:21,953
The side dishes are
simple but nice today.

90
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:23,020
Let's enjoy then, everyone.

91
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,900
- They're not that bad.
- No. Enjoy yourself.

92
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:36,520
I moved the braised beef
toward you.

93
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,866
Since you like meat.

94
00:05:41,966 --> 00:05:43,220
- Would you like water?
- Sure.

95
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:45,100
Thanks.

96
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,353
I moved the
stir-fried ham closer to you.

97
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:56,420
Because I know you like them.

98
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,153
Yes, I had some right away.

99
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,620
Enjoy your lunch, then.

100
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,733
Kwon.

101
00:06:00,933 --> 00:06:02,086
- Yes?
- Who are you texting,

102
00:06:02,166 --> 00:06:03,486
in the middle of your lunch?

103
00:06:03,566 --> 00:06:04,486
Yes, uh...

104
00:06:04,566 --> 00:06:06,433
My client keeps on texting me.

105
00:06:07,866 --> 00:06:11,253
You're so passionate
about your work that

106
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,353
you're working away,
even during your meals!

107
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:15,753
I must say you are my role model.

108
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:19,266
I really respect you. Right?

109
00:06:19,666 --> 00:06:20,933
I really respect you too, sir.

110
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,020
Stop your exaggeration.

111
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:25,886
There's a limit to everything.
Working even while eating?

112
00:06:25,966 --> 00:06:28,020
You know, I really think
Kwon's a workaholic.

113
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,253
Right, I'm sometimes worried
about you, Mr. Kwon,

114
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:31,986
because all you do is work.

115
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:34,286
Why? As long as he's happy.

116
00:06:34,366 --> 00:06:37,566
You truly enjoy
your work, don’t you?

117
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:39,766
Yes.

118
00:06:40,266 --> 00:06:41,800
With all my heart.

119
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:57,753
So you had something to tell me?

120
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,120
Well, uh...

121
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,086
That braised beef just now.

122
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:02,386
It was so delicious.

123
00:07:02,466 --> 00:07:03,500
What?

124
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:04,820
But...

125
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,733
But why tell me that here?

126
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,686
Well, uh...

127
00:07:08,766 --> 00:07:10,520
In the dramas,

128
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,986
office couples always meet up
at the emergency stairs,

129
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:15,600
so I always wanted to try it.

130
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,186
If you're free tonight,

131
00:07:19,266 --> 00:07:20,953
would you like to have
dinner with me?

132
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:23,053
Are you asking me out
on a date? Sure!

133
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:25,286
Then I'll make a reservation.

134
00:07:25,366 --> 00:07:26,366
Sure.

135
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:46,486
Can I get a printout of that
tax information submission order?

136
00:07:46,566 --> 00:07:48,653
Yes, Mr. Kwon. Right away, sir.

137
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,486
Get moving, then!
Why are you just standing here?

138
00:07:50,566 --> 00:07:51,566
Yes, sir.

139
00:07:52,766 --> 00:07:55,020
You must be anxious.

140
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,553
You know gambling is
against the law,

141
00:07:57,633 --> 00:08:00,320
yet you even went overseas for it.

142
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,153
But I'm sorry,
this may put you in despair

143
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:05,920
but because this isn't
your first time gambling,

144
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,300
it won't end with just
a light punishment.

145
00:08:11,566 --> 00:08:12,666
You know, I...

146
00:08:13,466 --> 00:08:17,000
I really hate myself for this.

147
00:08:18,566 --> 00:08:21,700
I know better than anyone else
that I really shouldn't,

148
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:24,786
but I keep falling into it,
every time...

149
00:08:24,866 --> 00:08:26,633
Right?

150
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:30,500
Why do I keep on falling...

151
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:32,666
I think it's crazy.

152
00:08:33,066 --> 00:08:35,286
What? Crazy?

153
00:08:35,366 --> 00:08:38,000
Don't you think that's
a little too harsh?

154
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:40,153
Um, uh...

155
00:08:40,233 --> 00:08:42,133
That wasn't meant for you.

156
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,266
I'm sorry.

157
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,820
Hae-young,

158
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,700
what's so funny?

159
00:09:06,266 --> 00:09:08,720
I'm learning
scuba diving these days,

160
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,553
with the friends I made
through an app.

161
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,453
And I was just looking at
the pictures from then.

162
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,320
You meet people through apps?

163
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,500
Yes.

164
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:22,353
You can meet people
who share your interests

165
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:23,986
on this app here.

166
00:09:24,066 --> 00:09:26,566
Why? Are you interested?

167
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:29,620
I keep having stray thoughts,

168
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,786
so I'd like to focus
my mind somewhere.

169
00:09:32,866 --> 00:09:34,420
I wonder if anyone's
interested in ukulele.

170
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,886
It'd be nice if I could find
someone to learn it with.

171
00:09:35,966 --> 00:09:38,320
Do you even have an ukulele?

172
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:41,120
Because I happen to have
a spare one.

173
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,566
You want to buy it off me?

174
00:09:44,866 --> 00:09:46,286
- What?
- I'll give you

175
00:09:46,366 --> 00:09:48,586
a special price for it.

176
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:50,433
I'll bring it someday, then.

177
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:53,120
No...

178
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,433
It's really alright.

179
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,600
I shouldn't get involved...

180
00:10:11,766 --> 00:10:14,153
So, is today a special day?

181
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:15,966
Why bring me to a place like this?

182
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:20,086
After searching for places
that aren't crowded,

183
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:21,820
all we did was go to
bad restaurants or

184
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,653
just stay in the car, so...

185
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:27,153
I wanted us to go on
a proper date.

186
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,333
I see.

187
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:33,086
You know, you really had me
back there.

188
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:37,920
I mean, you're kind of...
Dry, should I say?

189
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,920
So I thought you wouldn't like
making all those

190
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,720
secret exchanges while
everyone was there.

191
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,320
But you were really bold!

192
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:48,433
I didn't know I was capable of
such a thing myself.

193
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:52,166
But because you like it...

194
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:00,120
And as you said,

195
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,986
I wanted to make most of
the time we had remaining.

196
00:11:03,066 --> 00:11:05,320
Because there's only about
a month left for us to

197
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,833
enjoy this office romance.

198
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:17,733
Your plate is empty.

199
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:24,666
When did I finish everything?

200
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:29,400
You know, I think there's
a problem with this steak.

201
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:32,453
The dish is this big,
and the meat's only this size...

202
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:36,300
I mean, shouldn't the steak
take up at least half of the dish?

203
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:39,766
Can't they pass a law like that?

204
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:44,733
It will be difficult for
such a law to come into force,

205
00:11:47,066 --> 00:11:48,653
so have this for now.

206
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:50,766
That's not what I was aiming for.

207
00:11:50,966 --> 00:11:52,000
It's alright.

208
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,433
I'm fine.

209
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,100
I'm alright, too.

210
00:11:57,866 --> 00:11:58,866
Then...

211
00:11:59,466 --> 00:12:00,466
No, no. Stop.

212
00:12:03,366 --> 00:12:04,366
Go on.

213
00:12:05,566 --> 00:12:06,753
These days,

214
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:08,853
every day has been
a happy one for me.

215
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:12,966
Of course, the biggest reason is
that I have you with me.

216
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:16,586
To be honest,
when I first started out,

217
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:20,086
I was telling myself,
'Let's try and hold out somehow

218
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:21,866
for the next three months.'

219
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,786
But now,

220
00:12:23,866 --> 00:12:25,686
work is so much fun,

221
00:12:25,766 --> 00:12:27,200
and all the group dinners, too.

222
00:12:27,866 --> 00:12:29,486
Oh, and the workshop, too.

223
00:12:29,566 --> 00:12:31,820
Everything's just been
so much fun.

224
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:32,820
As Mr. Yeon said,

225
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:35,333
you're really like
Princess Ann from Roman Holiday.

226
00:12:35,766 --> 00:12:37,520
The princess who got tired of
her life in the palace,

227
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,666
and found happiness in the
small, day-to-day things.

228
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,320
You watched Roman Holiday?

229
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:47,753
I think I watched it on TV...

230
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:49,186
Come on, no!

231
00:12:49,266 --> 00:12:51,953
You should watch
Roman Holiday properly.

232
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:54,066
It's my favorite movie!

233
00:12:55,466 --> 00:12:58,286
Oh, I have a Blu-ray version at home.

234
00:12:58,366 --> 00:12:59,453
Would you like to
watch it with me?

235
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:01,353
Tomorrow's a Saturday, right?

236
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,766
Come over to my place.

237
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:04,433
- I'll do that, then.
- Yes.

238
00:13:05,033 --> 00:13:05,953
Hold on.

239
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,320
What did I just say?

240
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,753
Hold on.

241
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:12,153
So that means I'm going over to
Jin-sim's place.

242
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:13,386
Oh no!

243
00:13:13,466 --> 00:13:16,420
I only really invited him
over for the movie.

244
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,253
I only simply said yes
for the movie...

245
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,786
I hope she's not thinking...

246
00:13:20,866 --> 00:13:22,033
...That I have some
other intentions, right?

247
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,520
I need to pretend
everything's okay.

248
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,833
Otherwise it might make things
even more awkward.

249
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:36,486
Let's watch it tomorrow, then.

250
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:37,700
Sounds like fun!

251
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,433
- Yes, it does.
- Right?

252
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:45,000
Ah, I can't believe I'll be watching
Roman Holiday.

253
00:13:57,433 --> 00:13:58,433
You're home!

254
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:00,200
Did you have di...

255
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:02,933
What's with him?

256
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,366
Does he have something urgent
he needs to take care of?

257
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:15,800
I can't go empty-handed...

258
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:18,800
What should I take?

259
00:14:28,066 --> 00:14:29,633
(Visiting girlfriend)

260
00:14:32,166 --> 00:14:33,600
(When visiting girlfriend)

261
00:14:36,366 --> 00:14:38,100
(Guy's ultimate fantasy:
Visiting your girlfriend)

262
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,833
Oh what...

263
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:48,733
I'm only going over for the movie.

264
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:50,920
It's just that

265
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,453
we're going to be watching it
at her place, that's all.

266
00:15:27,266 --> 00:15:28,986
With that,

267
00:15:29,066 --> 00:15:31,433
he should say
my place is neat, right?

268
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:36,100
This is the first time
I'm having a boyfriend come over.

269
00:15:36,366 --> 00:15:37,533
I'm so nervous!

270
00:16:03,566 --> 00:16:05,366
Oh, my goodness. He must be here!

271
00:16:08,866 --> 00:16:09,953
Yes, hello?

272
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,586
It's me, Kwon Jung-rok…

273
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,533
Oh, that's right.

274
00:16:37,066 --> 00:16:38,066
Um...

275
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,133
- Come in.
- Sure.

276
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,953
Oh, and this too.

277
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,386
What's this?

278
00:17:09,466 --> 00:17:10,500
It's a gift.

279
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:13,286
You have trouble sleeping, right?

280
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:16,220
I heard that
a glass of wine helps.

281
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,586
Oh, thank you.

282
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:20,200
I'm really
looking forward to tonight.

283
00:17:21,266 --> 00:17:23,553
What was that you just said?

284
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:24,886
"Looking forward to tonight?"

285
00:17:24,966 --> 00:17:27,533
I really meant, I'm looking
forward to a good sleep.

286
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:29,933
I hope he didn't
interpret it otherwise.

287
00:17:32,866 --> 00:17:35,000
Sure, hope you have
a good sleep tonight.

288
00:17:36,266 --> 00:17:37,900
May I take this off?

289
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,720
Where's your object?

290
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:42,166
You should've said,
"May I take off my coat?"

291
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:45,633
You're a lawyer,
so where's your object?

292
00:17:46,266 --> 00:17:49,033
I hope she doesn't think
I have other intentions.

293
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,120
I meant my coat. My coat!

294
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,453
Yes, sure.

295
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:54,533
Thanks.

296
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,120
Um, may I put this here?

297
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,200
Sure.

298
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,286
You have a nice place.

299
00:18:11,366 --> 00:18:12,786
Then...

300
00:18:12,866 --> 00:18:14,620
Do you want me to show you around?

301
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:15,700
This way.

302
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:22,166
This is my study.

303
00:18:23,766 --> 00:18:25,253
It's my favorite place

304
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,866
in the house.

305
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:32,286
You have a lot of books.

306
00:18:32,366 --> 00:18:34,666
Of course. I love reading.

307
00:18:37,666 --> 00:18:40,020
Oh my goodness!

308
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,653
You'd think that, uh...

309
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:44,153
Dust has piled up because
I never take out books from here,

310
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:45,286
but that's not the case!

311
00:18:45,366 --> 00:18:47,600
I read often,
but just don't dust often.

312
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,200
I dust often, but I don't...

313
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:53,533
I mean...

314
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,166
Anyway, let's move on.

315
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:08,133
This is my bedroom.

316
00:19:08,966 --> 00:19:10,433
Isn't this a nice dressing table?

317
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,720
I just love this bed, too.

318
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,520
You don't find
designs like this often.

319
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:18,620
The headpiece is just the
right height,

320
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,800
and the mattress is so soft, too.

321
00:19:21,466 --> 00:19:25,086
Oh what? Why am I describing the
bed with such detail?

322
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:27,886
The mattress is so soft...
So what?

323
00:19:27,966 --> 00:19:29,966
It's not like I'm inviting him to
lie here with me.

324
00:19:30,566 --> 00:19:33,666
I hope he didn't take it that way!

325
00:19:38,733 --> 00:19:40,286
Oh what?
Why did I turn off the lights?

326
00:19:40,366 --> 00:19:41,386
This is the bedroom!

327
00:19:41,466 --> 00:19:42,966
Why did I make such a mistake?

328
00:19:44,866 --> 00:19:45,900
My hand slipped.

329
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:49,566
Sure, of course.

330
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,500
Then shall we go to
the kitchen next?

331
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:05,200
Yes, I'll send my opinions
through mail.

332
00:20:05,466 --> 00:20:07,500
If you've anything to add,
then please write back.

333
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:08,900
Sure.

334
00:20:11,766 --> 00:20:13,920
- Ah, Ms. Dan.
- Mr. Choi.

335
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,653
Why are you here on the weekend?

336
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:17,820
I had preparing to do
before the trial.

337
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:19,133
What about you?

338
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:21,833
I had some work to do, too.

339
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:24,753
Ah, great.

340
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:27,786
I brought the ukulele
that I told you about.

341
00:20:27,866 --> 00:20:30,700
I'll bring it to your room later.

342
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:40,086
Oh what?

343
00:20:40,166 --> 00:20:41,686
Just us two, in the office
on the weekend?

344
00:20:41,766 --> 00:20:42,866
Is this what they call...

345
00:20:44,766 --> 00:20:45,766
...destiny?

346
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,633
Destiny? Whatever!

347
00:20:48,933 --> 00:20:50,520
Get a grip on yourself,
Dan Mun-hee.

348
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,000
You decided to stop doing this!

349
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,620
Ms. Dan,

350
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,366
here's the ukulele
I told you about.

351
00:21:08,866 --> 00:21:10,886
Ah, how much do you want for this?

352
00:21:10,966 --> 00:21:12,000
It's alright.

353
00:21:12,466 --> 00:21:14,220
Just buy me a drink sometime.

354
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:15,486
A drink?

355
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:16,566
Yes.

356
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:19,700
Then... Here you are.

357
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,353
Thanks for everything until now.

358
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:26,666
You were once a part of me,

359
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:29,620
and me, a part of you...

360
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:32,633
All those harmonies
we created together,

361
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:34,933
as one...

362
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:38,500
I'll never forget them.

363
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:45,600
So instead of goodbye,
let me play this tune...

364
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,000
Alright, I'm done with
my goodbyes.

365
00:22:32,866 --> 00:22:34,220
Here you are, then.

366
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:35,866
Thank you.

367
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:37,800
Take good care of it for me.

368
00:22:40,166 --> 00:22:42,686
Oh, do you even know
how to play an ukulele?

369
00:22:42,766 --> 00:22:46,466
Well, I took some
lessons before...

370
00:22:47,166 --> 00:22:49,566
I know some chords.

371
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:54,900
The... The C-chord...

372
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,333
The F-chord...

373
00:22:59,566 --> 00:23:01,600
You're even holding it wrong.

374
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:04,933
Here.

375
00:23:06,266 --> 00:23:07,266
Here.

376
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,833
Relax your shoulders.

377
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:17,000
And hold this ukulele gently like
you're holding a child.

378
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:20,366
Like this.

379
00:23:27,433 --> 00:23:28,966
Please!

380
00:23:30,466 --> 00:23:32,166
Give me your permission!

381
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,300
I...

382
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:38,000
I want to love him!

383
00:23:38,466 --> 00:23:39,933
Mr. Choi!

384
00:23:45,433 --> 00:23:48,486
I see you watch movies often
in your place.

385
00:23:48,566 --> 00:23:51,486
Yes, I love watching movies.

386
00:23:51,566 --> 00:23:52,600
Sure.

387
00:23:53,466 --> 00:23:54,466
Oh.

388
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:57,853
One minute.

389
00:23:57,933 --> 00:23:58,933
Sure.

390
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:00,366
Yes, hello? Prosecutor?

391
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,600
Yes.

392
00:24:03,666 --> 00:24:06,133
Next Wednesday for me is a bit...

393
00:24:06,866 --> 00:24:08,200
No, it's not that.

394
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:14,600
What...

395
00:24:15,633 --> 00:24:16,633
Huh?

396
00:24:18,166 --> 00:24:19,966
Where did it go?
It was right here!

397
00:24:21,766 --> 00:24:23,333
It's not here.

398
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:31,486
Hey, Hyuk-jun.

399
00:24:31,566 --> 00:24:33,753
My Blu-ray disc player is gone.

400
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:34,933
What happened?

401
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:37,033
What? You took it to be repaired?

402
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,000
Why didn't you tell me before...

403
00:24:39,266 --> 00:24:40,686
...doing that?

404
00:24:40,766 --> 00:24:43,086
What? But I always just
took care of

405
00:24:43,166 --> 00:24:44,920
whatever that needs
fixing at your place.

406
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,653
So what's this, all of a sudden?

407
00:24:46,733 --> 00:24:48,633
What do I do now?

408
00:24:49,733 --> 00:24:50,900
Oh, alright. Talk to you later.

409
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:55,566
Are we going to watch it now?

410
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,133
Um...

411
00:25:00,966 --> 00:25:02,153
No...

412
00:25:02,233 --> 00:25:03,386
No?

413
00:25:03,466 --> 00:25:04,386
Oh.

414
00:25:04,466 --> 00:25:06,953
You mean, I might not enjoy it?

415
00:25:07,033 --> 00:25:07,953
That's alright.

416
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:10,486
Though I don't really
watch movies,

417
00:25:10,566 --> 00:25:11,986
since this is your favorite,

418
00:25:12,066 --> 00:25:13,633
I'll try my best.

419
00:25:14,233 --> 00:25:16,953
No, what I mean is...

420
00:25:17,033 --> 00:25:21,266
I don't have the player.

421
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:28,686
I must've forgotten
I took it to be repaired.

422
00:25:28,766 --> 00:25:30,466
Oh, I see.

423
00:25:38,333 --> 00:25:40,566
How about the laptop...

424
00:25:46,566 --> 00:25:49,786
How about we watch it
on the laptop instead?

425
00:25:49,866 --> 00:25:51,286
I'll download it right away.

426
00:25:51,366 --> 00:25:52,320
Don't mind me,

427
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,566
take your time.

428
00:25:56,233 --> 00:25:57,266
Go on.

429
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,353
Oh, I'd been curious
about those trophies.

430
00:26:05,433 --> 00:26:06,920
May I take a look?

431
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,366
Oh, sure.

432
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:18,720
KBC Award,
MBU Hot Celebrity Award,

433
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:22,200
TBM Teenager's Choice,
SBC People's Choice...

434
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:25,333
Wow, that's a lot of awards.

435
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:28,053
I did, yes.

436
00:26:28,133 --> 00:26:30,233
Though the problem is,
it's all thanks to my popularity.

437
00:26:31,466 --> 00:26:32,966
Why is that a problem?

438
00:26:34,166 --> 00:26:35,166
Well...

439
00:26:38,233 --> 00:26:39,986
None are for my acting,

440
00:26:40,066 --> 00:26:42,800
so I'm embarrassed they're
all for my popularity.

441
00:26:43,033 --> 00:26:44,833
Why should you be embarrassed
about it?

442
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,553
Your popularity means

443
00:26:46,633 --> 00:26:48,886
that many people like you.

444
00:26:48,966 --> 00:26:50,820
And I think winning over
someone's heart is

445
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:53,000
something that's very difficult.

446
00:26:53,433 --> 00:26:54,733
So I think you're amazing.

447
00:26:55,833 --> 00:26:57,033
You think so?

448
00:26:58,533 --> 00:26:59,553
But you know,

449
00:26:59,633 --> 00:27:01,053
I think if I can
go back to acting now...

450
00:27:01,133 --> 00:27:03,700
I'll really pull it off this time.

451
00:27:03,866 --> 00:27:07,620
Because back then,
I didn't really know

452
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:09,053
the excitement of being in love.

453
00:27:09,133 --> 00:27:12,286
And because I didn't know,
I couldn't really express it.

454
00:27:12,366 --> 00:27:13,433
But now...

455
00:27:15,533 --> 00:27:16,533
But now,

456
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:18,966
I think I have an idea.

457
00:27:31,366 --> 00:27:34,253
What drama is that picture from?

458
00:27:34,333 --> 00:27:35,433
You look beautiful in this picture.

459
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,886
That wasn't a drama.

460
00:27:38,966 --> 00:27:41,666
I made my debut through that
chocolate commercial.

461
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:45,220
Thanks to that commercial,
all the chocolates sold out

462
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:48,786
and they even dubbed me
the "chocolate fairy."

463
00:27:48,866 --> 00:27:50,800
And you're telling me
you never saw it?

464
00:27:51,966 --> 00:27:52,886
I can't have this.

465
00:27:52,966 --> 00:27:55,020
This is no time to watch
Roman Holiday, then.

466
00:27:55,100 --> 00:27:57,386
Come on, over here.

467
00:27:57,466 --> 00:27:58,553
Come sit, now!

468
00:27:58,633 --> 00:27:59,633
Sure.

469
00:28:10,233 --> 00:28:11,220
Look here.

470
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:13,266
Don't I look so cute
and adorable here?

471
00:28:16,633 --> 00:28:18,653
And this, too.
Don't I look pretty?

472
00:28:18,733 --> 00:28:19,866
And so innocent, right?

473
00:28:22,733 --> 00:28:24,253
So beautiful.

474
00:28:24,333 --> 00:28:26,100
Don't I just look elegant?

475
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:30,753
Do you want to see
my photos, too?

476
00:28:30,833 --> 00:28:33,000
- Oh, this?
- Yes, want to take a look?

477
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:43,686
I didn't know it back then,

478
00:28:43,766 --> 00:28:45,833
but I was quite pretty.

479
00:28:46,566 --> 00:28:47,633
Right?

480
00:28:50,366 --> 00:28:51,453
Come to think of it,

481
00:28:51,533 --> 00:28:53,133
why haven't I heard you
agree with me?

482
00:28:54,666 --> 00:28:55,720
What, you don’t think I'm pretty?

483
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,066
No, I think you're pretty.

484
00:28:57,866 --> 00:28:59,833
But I think you're prettier now.

485
00:29:00,666 --> 00:29:02,566
The you, who's in front of me.

486
00:29:10,166 --> 00:29:11,120
Um,

487
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:12,533
can I have this?

488
00:29:12,933 --> 00:29:14,686
- This?
- Yes.

489
00:29:14,766 --> 00:29:16,353
Though I want everything,

490
00:29:16,433 --> 00:29:17,833
I can't really do that, but...

491
00:29:18,100 --> 00:29:20,600
But I really must have this one.

492
00:29:21,900 --> 00:29:24,033
Alright, then. Take it with you.

493
00:29:24,733 --> 00:29:25,686
You know, I'll be generous.

494
00:29:25,766 --> 00:29:26,686
You can pick one more.

495
00:29:26,766 --> 00:29:28,953
- Oh, sure.
- They're all worth keeping,

496
00:29:29,033 --> 00:29:31,066
so you need to pick carefully.

497
00:29:32,333 --> 00:29:34,133
So this is the chocolate...

498
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:48,420
Ah, so fragrant!

499
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,100
I'm glad you like it.

500
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,153
It's really too bad, though.

501
00:29:56,233 --> 00:29:58,086
I invited you over for the movie,

502
00:29:58,166 --> 00:30:00,786
but we never got to see it.

503
00:30:00,866 --> 00:30:01,920
I'm really sorry.

504
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,486
No, I'm actually glad that

505
00:30:03,566 --> 00:30:05,853
we never got to see the movie.

506
00:30:05,933 --> 00:30:06,933
What?

507
00:30:09,466 --> 00:30:12,153
To be honest,

508
00:30:12,233 --> 00:30:13,866
I didn't sleep a wink last night.

509
00:30:15,066 --> 00:30:16,953
I was nervous.

510
00:30:17,033 --> 00:30:19,453
When I thought about how
I'll be visiting your place,

511
00:30:19,533 --> 00:30:22,533
I still couldn't believe it
and was a little nervous.

512
00:30:23,466 --> 00:30:24,833
And of course, a little excited.

513
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:28,533
- Same with me!
- Huh?

514
00:30:29,966 --> 00:30:32,053
When I thought about
how you'll be coming over,

515
00:30:32,133 --> 00:30:35,220
I was so nervous that
my heart was beating fast!

516
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,986
And you know how
I have insomnia, right?

517
00:30:38,066 --> 00:30:40,966
Well, yesterday I ended up
not getting any sleep at all!

518
00:30:42,733 --> 00:30:45,686
Gosh, I thought it was just me.

519
00:30:45,766 --> 00:30:47,586
No, I was like that too.

520
00:30:47,666 --> 00:30:49,953
Anyway, though I was
nervous at first,

521
00:30:50,033 --> 00:30:53,186
that's all gone away thanks to

522
00:30:53,266 --> 00:30:54,586
all that time we spent
chatting over your pretty photos.

523
00:30:54,666 --> 00:30:57,020
Same for me, too!

524
00:30:57,100 --> 00:31:00,800
I only got over it after
we looked at the photos together.

525
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:04,853
Before then, all kinds of
things ran in my head

526
00:31:04,933 --> 00:31:06,520
when you were here and

527
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:09,400
I realized it's just us two,
here alone...

528
00:31:14,366 --> 00:31:16,753
But that doesn't mean

529
00:31:16,833 --> 00:31:19,866
I was having naughty thoughts.

530
00:31:22,433 --> 00:31:24,666
By naughty thoughts,
do you mean...

531
00:31:25,766 --> 00:31:27,400
Well, uh...

532
00:31:34,466 --> 00:31:36,100
Do you mean something like this?

533
00:31:39,300 --> 00:31:40,333
Or...

534
00:31:42,100 --> 00:31:43,166
Something like this?

535
00:32:11,633 --> 00:32:12,666
Hey, Hyuk-jun.

536
00:32:13,966 --> 00:32:15,286
