withdraw his retaliatory order!)

795
00:47:01,100 --> 00:47:03,453
No need to sigh.

796
00:47:03,533 --> 00:47:07,386
I'm actually relieved that
I've been suspended.

797
00:47:07,466 --> 00:47:08,386
Just what do you...

798
00:47:08,466 --> 00:47:11,653
Despite my whistle-blowing,
nothing's changed.

799
00:47:11,733 --> 00:47:14,233
Everyone around me was
trying to cover this up.

800
00:47:14,833 --> 00:47:18,020
But now that they've
suspended me for 3 months,

801
00:47:18,100 --> 00:47:21,000
they've given me an excuse
for this protest.

802
00:47:21,966 --> 00:47:23,000
This may be a chance

803
00:47:23,633 --> 00:47:26,800
for the world to know
more about this.

804
00:47:30,533 --> 00:47:32,766
Have you filed for appeal?
(Appeals: Administrative trial to review disciplinary action)

805
00:47:33,566 --> 00:47:35,053
When is the review?
(of public officials or unfavorable disposition)

806
00:47:35,133 --> 00:47:36,166
Tomorrow.

807
00:47:37,300 --> 00:47:39,000
And what if your suspension is fixed?

808
00:47:40,533 --> 00:47:43,153
Then I'll have to take it to Court.

809
00:47:43,233 --> 00:47:45,400
Is that why you were
in my office earlier?

810
00:47:47,500 --> 00:47:49,020
To ask me to defend you,

811
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:51,333
if you end up
taking this to the Court?

812
00:47:55,300 --> 00:47:57,533
Then you should've said so
from the beginning.

813
00:47:59,133 --> 00:48:00,653
Did you even give me a chance to

814
00:48:00,733 --> 00:48:02,566
ask you that?

815
00:48:03,466 --> 00:48:05,553
Still, you just walked out.

816
00:48:05,633 --> 00:48:07,733
You always make me the bad son.

817
00:48:19,233 --> 00:48:21,100
I see, so that's what happened.

818
00:48:23,533 --> 00:48:25,686
With all these things going on,

819
00:48:25,766 --> 00:48:28,433
I had to suspect him for
something like that...

820
00:48:31,500 --> 00:48:34,053
Don't worry too much,
I'm sure it's nothing.

821
00:48:34,133 --> 00:48:35,820
Even if they decide on
his suspension,

822
00:48:35,900 --> 00:48:37,686
we'll have that
overturned in Court.

823
00:48:37,766 --> 00:48:40,286
I'm going to do all I can to
set everything right,

824
00:48:40,366 --> 00:48:42,166
so there's no more
need for you to worry.

825
00:48:45,666 --> 00:48:46,900
It's really okay.

826
00:48:47,533 --> 00:48:48,986
No...

827
00:48:49,066 --> 00:48:51,320
There's that too, but...

828
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:56,253
I'm worried about
what he thinks of me now.

829
00:48:56,333 --> 00:48:59,453
If he finds out that you're seeing
an actress with such a past...

830
00:48:59,533 --> 00:49:01,100
He'll be worried.

831
00:49:02,733 --> 00:49:05,233
And I just had to leave
a bad first impression.

832
00:49:10,733 --> 00:49:12,500
No need to be so sad about it.

833
00:49:14,133 --> 00:49:16,320
Because once anyone learns
what you're truly like,

834
00:49:16,400 --> 00:49:18,420
they can't help but like you.

835
00:49:18,500 --> 00:49:21,266
There must be a reason why you
won all those popularity awards.

836
00:49:30,100 --> 00:49:33,353
Then will it be just your father
at the disciplinary review?

837
00:49:33,433 --> 00:49:35,120
Yes, well...

838
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:36,853
He just needs to
state his opinions and

839
00:49:36,933 --> 00:49:39,420
hear their decision,

840
00:49:39,500 --> 00:49:41,833
so there's no need for me to
accompany him.

841
00:49:43,433 --> 00:49:44,666
I see.

842
00:49:45,166 --> 00:49:46,166
But...

843
00:49:47,033 --> 00:49:49,800
Won't he be nervous about
going alone?

844
00:49:54,133 --> 00:49:56,553
What? You think
I should accompany him?

845
00:49:56,633 --> 00:49:57,820
No matter how I think about it,

846
00:49:57,900 --> 00:50:00,186
I think your father will feel
too nervous on his own.

847
00:50:00,266 --> 00:50:02,286
So I think it's best that
you accompany him,

848
00:50:02,366 --> 00:50:05,320
as his son and his lawyer.

849
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:07,953
I re-arranged all your
appointments for this morning,

850
00:50:08,033 --> 00:50:09,233
so off you go.

851
00:50:10,100 --> 00:50:11,320
Thanks for your consideration,

852
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:14,253
but you don't know my father.

853
00:50:14,333 --> 00:50:17,086
My father's not someone to
get nervous over such a thing.

854
00:50:17,166 --> 00:50:19,453
He's got a strong mentality.

855
00:50:19,533 --> 00:50:21,886
That's what you think.

856
00:50:21,966 --> 00:50:25,986
Even if he is a strong person,
this must be all new to him.

857
00:50:26,066 --> 00:50:28,253
He might get nervous,

858
00:50:28,333 --> 00:50:31,466
and may need someone to
rely on, who knows?

859
00:50:37,033 --> 00:50:40,233
So go, just this one. Come on!

860
00:50:41,066 --> 00:50:42,720
I'm just really worried that

861
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:45,400
you two ended up having
an argument because of me.

862
00:50:46,966 --> 00:50:50,820
So please, for my sake.

863
00:50:50,900 --> 00:50:52,366
Yes, well...

864
00:50:53,900 --> 00:50:56,000
Alright, then let's go!

865
00:50:59,633 --> 00:51:00,553
Here.

866
00:51:00,633 --> 00:51:03,133
Take this. This is to help
calm the nerves.

867
00:51:03,833 --> 00:51:05,220
Though it's a little old and

868
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:06,986
I don't look like the person to
carry these around...

869
00:51:07,066 --> 00:51:09,820
Nothing beats that when
you're in a nervous situation.

870
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:12,786
Then have a good trip.

871
00:51:12,866 --> 00:51:13,900
Off you go!

872
00:51:14,333 --> 00:51:15,900
Let's go.

873
00:51:47,233 --> 00:51:48,466
I'm here.

874
00:51:50,433 --> 00:51:51,566
Why did you come here?

875
00:51:54,400 --> 00:51:56,766
My morning appointment was
cancelled, so...

876
00:51:58,233 --> 00:52:00,500
You must have more free time
than I thought.

877
00:52:03,900 --> 00:52:06,720
Everything is ready,
including written opinions,

878
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:08,266
so it should all be fine.

879
00:52:17,433 --> 00:52:20,053
Even if you do end up
taking this to Court,

880
00:52:20,133 --> 00:52:22,553
I will win this case no matter what.

881
00:52:22,633 --> 00:52:24,066
So don't worry too much.

882
00:52:26,900 --> 00:52:28,686
I'm not worried.

883
00:52:28,766 --> 00:52:30,233
Of course that's how it should be.

884
00:52:38,433 --> 00:52:41,466
I've something for your nerves.
Would you like it?

885
00:52:52,033 --> 00:52:53,200
If you have something,
give it to me.

886
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:45,800
They should be done by now...

887
00:53:50,066 --> 00:53:52,353
Mr. Kwon, how did it go?

888
00:53:52,433 --> 00:53:55,100
His suspension has been confirmed.

889
00:53:57,700 --> 00:54:00,853
We'll have to start working
on it right away.

890
00:54:00,933 --> 00:54:02,286
And,

891
00:54:02,366 --> 00:54:04,053
it's as you said.

892
00:54:04,133 --> 00:54:06,686
I'm glad I was there for
my father today.

893
00:54:06,766 --> 00:54:10,086
That tonic you gave to me
was a big help, too.

894
00:54:10,166 --> 00:54:12,053
Thank you for your
kind consideration.

895
00:54:12,133 --> 00:54:14,753
It's nothing.

896
00:54:14,833 --> 00:54:16,820
Cheer your father up, then.

897
00:54:16,900 --> 00:54:19,520
Don't talk back like that

898
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:22,420
and take him
somewhere nice for lunch.

899
00:54:22,500 --> 00:54:23,500
Oh, and...

900
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:27,186
If you have the chance,

901
00:54:27,266 --> 00:54:32,286
maybe mention that it was me
who got him that tonic?

902
00:54:32,366 --> 00:54:34,633
Yes, alright.

903
00:54:46,233 --> 00:54:48,166
(Evidence)

904
00:54:49,400 --> 00:54:51,766
(Affidavit)

905
00:54:57,366 --> 00:54:59,486
I've just spoken with the Chief.

906
00:54:59,566 --> 00:55:01,733
Why? Did he want you to
try and stop me?

907
00:55:03,166 --> 00:55:05,520
Let me make this clear
so I don't waste your time,

908
00:55:05,600 --> 00:55:07,033
but don't try to convince me.

909
00:55:08,433 --> 00:55:10,453
What if you really get into
the DA's bad books?

910
00:55:10,533 --> 00:55:12,420
You only just managed to
come back, too.

911
00:55:12,500 --> 00:55:14,453
At this rate, you really might...

912
00:55:14,533 --> 00:55:16,700
I said, don't try to convince me.

913
00:55:54,800 --> 00:55:56,266
Don't you think that
this makes us even.

914
00:55:57,066 --> 00:55:58,220
Pay me back properly.

915
00:55:58,300 --> 00:56:01,266
Don't worry, I have a conscience.

916
00:56:08,233 --> 00:56:09,266
So, what's this about?

917
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:11,733
Did something happen?

918
00:56:17,700 --> 00:56:18,733
Yu Yeo-reum.

919
00:56:20,633 --> 00:56:22,066
Can you hug me, just this once?

920
00:56:23,733 --> 00:56:24,900
What's this about?

921
00:56:29,133 --> 00:56:30,166
Just...

922
00:56:31,433 --> 00:56:32,533
I just...

923
00:56:33,966 --> 00:56:35,066
I just wish that

924
00:56:38,033 --> 00:56:40,000
you'll comfort me.

925
00:57:16,300 --> 00:57:18,253
(The Disciplinary
Committee's Decision)

926
00:57:18,333 --> 00:57:20,366
(Vice Mayor
Kim Jun-cheol's 1.2 million...)

927
00:57:23,700 --> 00:57:27,020
Here, your favorite.
Instant coffee mix.

928
00:57:27,100 --> 00:57:28,786
Thank you.

929
00:57:28,866 --> 00:57:31,453
Is everything going alright
with the trial?

930
00:57:31,533 --> 00:57:32,533
Yes.

931
00:57:33,166 --> 00:57:36,586
At first, I thought he was
making a big deal out of nothing

932
00:57:36,666 --> 00:57:38,620
but as I dug deeper into this,

933
00:57:38,700 --> 00:57:41,186
I came to understand
why he did what he did.

934
00:57:41,266 --> 00:57:44,520
Because though everyone might
think he's making a fuss,

935
00:57:44,600 --> 00:57:47,153
the right thing here is to
right what's wrong.

936
00:57:47,233 --> 00:57:48,220
Yes, right.

937
00:57:48,300 --> 00:57:51,020
I also respect
your father for that.

938
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:52,586
Because it wouldn't have been
easy to be the whistleblower

939
00:57:52,666 --> 00:57:55,033
if you learned that sort of thing.

940
00:57:55,700 --> 00:57:59,353
I really admire him for that.

941
00:57:59,433 --> 00:58:03,733
So be good to your father,
who's truly amazing.

942
00:58:05,466 --> 00:58:10,053
Oh, and if you ever
have the chance,

943
00:58:10,133 --> 00:58:12,533
please mention that it was me
who advised you to be good to him.

944
00:58:13,866 --> 00:58:15,853
Does it concern you that much?

945
00:58:15,933 --> 00:58:17,953
That you might have left
a bad impression on him?

946
00:58:18,033 --> 00:58:21,433
Of course I'm concerned.

947
00:58:23,666 --> 00:58:26,266
Alright. I'll make sure to
pass it on.

948
00:58:37,033 --> 00:58:38,986
Here we have a public servant,

949
00:58:39,066 --> 00:58:41,200
who happens to be my client
and my father.

950
00:58:42,066 --> 00:58:43,820
And in the past 30 years,

951
00:58:43,900 --> 00:58:47,020
he has never been suspended.

952
00:58:47,100 --> 00:58:49,686
Yet, right before his retirement,

953
00:58:49,766 --> 00:58:51,420
he has been suspended for
three months, for

954
00:58:51,500 --> 00:58:55,286
raising suspicions that
his boss may have

955
00:58:55,366 --> 00:58:58,020
embezzled $2.7 million.

956
00:58:58,100 --> 00:58:59,320
Your Honor,

957
00:58:59,400 --> 00:59:02,253
the Civil Servant's Charter
stipulates that

958
00:59:02,333 --> 00:59:03,853
a civil servant must
prioritize common good,

959
00:59:03,933 --> 00:59:05,020
and assume
his full responsibilities

960
00:59:05,100 --> 00:59:08,253
in a fair and
transparent manner.

961
00:59:08,333 --> 00:59:11,120
Article 15 of the
Whistleblowing Protection Law

962
00:59:11,200 --> 00:59:14,553
also states that no person shall
implement any disadvantageous

963
00:59:14,633 --> 00:59:17,720
measures against the whistleblower
in retaliation.

964
00:59:17,800 --> 00:59:19,020
As for what truly

965
00:59:19,100 --> 00:59:22,153
befits the description of justice
as discussed by countless books

966
00:59:22,233 --> 00:59:24,053
on law, I hope you, Your Honor,

967
00:59:24,133 --> 00:59:26,366
will make a wise decision on that.

968
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:28,166
I rest my case.

969
00:59:51,000 --> 00:59:52,100
Thanks for that.

970
00:59:52,700 --> 00:59:53,766
It's nothing.

971
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:56,466
Please excuse me.

972
00:59:59,566 --> 01:00:00,920
Mr. Kwon.

973
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:03,253
You were amazing today.

974
01:00:03,333 --> 01:00:07,153
I'm sure you made
your father proud.

975
01:00:07,233 --> 01:00:08,486
I'll get going first,

976
01:00:08,566 --> 01:00:11,033
so enjoy your lunch
with your father.

977
01:00:13,100 --> 01:00:14,986
Let's go for lunch, then.

978
01:00:15,066 --> 01:00:16,686
Sure.

979
01:00:16,766 --> 01:00:19,333
With my secretary,
Ms. Oh Jin-sim as well.

980
01:00:21,900 --> 01:00:23,066
Will that be okay?

981
01:00:30,700 --> 01:00:32,053
What?

982
01:00:32,133 --> 01:00:35,320
Why does he suddenly want me to
join him for lunch with his father?

983
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:36,586
Well, this is my last chance to

984
01:00:36,666 --> 01:00:38,753
make up for that
grave mistake that I made.

985
01:00:38,833 --> 01:00:39,866
Right?

986
01:00:41,600 --> 01:00:44,900
I'm already calmly
dressed in black,

987
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:48,333
but are my lips too pink?

988
01:00:54,966 --> 01:00:57,553
Today, I have to be
serious and careful.

989
01:00:57,633 --> 01:00:59,086
Let's watch yourself today.

990
01:00:59,166 --> 01:01:00,966
Be serious,
and watch your actions.

991
01:01:03,866 --> 01:01:05,366
No, not like that.

992
01:01:21,600 --> 01:01:23,720
What I learnt from this case is,

993
01:01:23,800 --> 01:01:26,520
you can't prevent corruption by

994
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:28,153
punishing the officers
down the hierarchy.

995
01:01:28,233 --> 01:01:29,833
You need to uproot its very cause!

996
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:33,820
The disciplinary system
in place right now,

997
01:01:33,900 --> 01:01:36,466
is all just for show.

998
01:01:37,166 --> 01:01:38,266
I completely agree.

999
01:01:40,866 --> 01:01:43,353
Just like these useless
decorations right here,

1000
01:01:43,433 --> 01:01:46,353
I believe they're the result of
window-dressing policies.

1001
01:01:46,433 --> 01:01:50,120
And that's led to this
vicious cycle,

1002
01:01:50,200 --> 01:01:52,566
where I've now been victimized.

1003
01:01:55,233 --> 01:02:00,653
Ah, I'm sorry we've been
lost in boring talk.

1004
01:02:00,733 --> 01:02:02,786
No, not at all.
It's interesting to hear.

1005
01:02:02,866 --> 01:02:05,420
Tell him honestly,
that it's boring.

1006
01:02:05,500 --> 01:02:08,200
No, no. It's interesting. Really.

1007
01:02:11,233 --> 01:02:13,720
By the way, Ms. Oh Jin-sim

1008
01:02:13,800 --> 01:02:16,966
asked me to mention
some things to you.

1009
01:02:20,566 --> 01:02:23,453
It was she who cancelled
all my morning appointments

1010
01:02:23,533 --> 01:02:26,766
and told me to be there
with you for the review.

1011
01:02:27,800 --> 01:02:31,753
She also bought that tonic,

1012
01:02:31,833 --> 01:02:34,120
and said I should be
a better son to you,

1013
01:02:34,200 --> 01:02:37,986
since you're such
a respectful father.

1014
01:02:38,066 --> 01:02:40,120
That's Ms. Oh Jin-sim, right here.

1015
01:02:40,200 --> 01:02:41,586
Uh, Mr. Kwon?

1016
01:02:41,666 --> 01:02:45,820
That's how considerate she is.

1017
01:02:45,900 --> 01:02:47,320
Which is why,

1018
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:50,020
I like her very much.

1019
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:51,400
Let me introduce her to you.

1020
01:02:52,733 --> 01:02:53,900
This is my girlfriend.

1021
01:03:04,400 --> 01:03:07,133
Is that something to be
so shocked about?

1022
01:03:08,200 --> 01:03:09,333
Of course!

1023
01:03:10,200 --> 01:03:11,320
I've never seen you act like this,

1024
01:03:11,400 --> 01:03:13,620
confessing your love for a girl
in front of me!

1025
01:03:13,700 --> 01:03:16,320
Of course I would be shocked.

1026
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:19,120
Right? I'm in such a panic, too.

1027
01:03:19,200 --> 01:03:21,820
Right? I'm not the only one
who's panicking here, is it?

1028
01:03:21,900 --> 01:03:25,220
No! You know your son
better than anyone else.

1029
01:03:25,300 --> 01:03:26,786
He's never the person to do
such a thing.

1030
01:03:26,866 --> 01:03:28,666
Exactly!

1031
01:03:31,166 --> 01:03:33,433
So your name is Oh Jin-sim?

1032
01:03:35,233 --> 01:03:36,266
Yes.

1033
01:03:38,133 --> 01:03:40,886
For my son to do
something like that,

1034
01:03:40,966 --> 01:03:44,566
he must sure like you a lot.

1035
01:03:46,466 --> 01:03:48,620
Please take good care of my son,

1036
01:03:48,700 --> 01:03:51,400
though he needs a lot of work.

1037
01:03:52,100 --> 01:03:53,753
No, not at all!

1038
01:03:53,833 --> 01:03:56,353
He's not like that all,
he's just perfect.

1039
01:03:56,433 --> 01:04:00,620
I'll make your dear son happy,

1040
01:04:00,700 --> 01:04:02,100
so don't worry, Mr. Kwon, sir.

1041
01:04:13,800 --> 01:04:16,100
- Let's eat, then.
- Alright.

1042
01:04:19,533 --> 01:04:22,253
You had me panicking
so much back there!

1043
01:04:22,333 --> 01:04:25,820
Who knew you'd be
so straight like that?

1044
01:04:25,900 --> 01:04:27,086
Did I embarrass you?

1045
01:04:27,166 --> 01:04:28,920
Embarrass me?

1046
01:04:29,000 --> 01:04:31,053
No, I was more touched!

1047
01:04:31,133 --> 01:04:32,986
That should be my line.

1048
01:04:33,066 --> 01:04:35,533
You've done so much for me
and my father.

1049
01:04:36,966 --> 01:04:39,986
We both have high pride,
so whenever we argued,

1050
01:04:40,066 --> 01:04:43,786
we'd go months without
calling each other.

1051
01:04:43,866 --> 01:04:46,586
My mother always had a hard time
between us.

1052
01:04:46,666 --> 01:04:51,186
But thanks to you this time,
we were able to make up quickly.

1053
01:04:51,266 --> 01:04:53,120
I'm sure my father is
grateful to you on that.

1054
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:54,366
Really?

1055
01:04:56,100 --> 01:05:00,153
Mr. Kwon, I really like
how we're an office couple.

1056
01:05:00,233 --> 01:05:02,786
Especially after this incident!

1057
01:05:02,866 --> 01:05:04,220
Because we work at the same place,

1058
01:05:04,300 --> 01:05:06,353
I was able to meet your father,

1059
01:05:06,433 --> 01:05:09,653
and help you to
make up with him.

1060
01:05:09,733 --> 01:05:13,453
And earn his approval, too!

1061
01:05:13,533 --> 01:05:15,766
Anyway, I like everything about it.

1062
01:05:22,233 --> 01:05:23,300
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

1063
01:05:33,066 --> 01:05:34,900
What's this?

1064
01:05:37,266 --> 01:05:38,866
Gosh, it's so pretty.

1065
01:05:42,333 --> 01:05:44,553
- But why...
- It's a gift for you.

1066
01:05:44,633 --> 01:05:45,933
A gift?

1067
01:05:46,966 --> 01:05:50,386
Is this to thank me for helping
you to make up with your father?

1068
01:05:50,466 --> 01:05:52,120
No, it's not like that.

1069
01:05:52,200 --> 01:05:54,133
I just wanted to give it to you.

1070
01:06:14,066 --> 01:06:16,020
Beautiful.

1071
01:06:16,100 --> 01:06:17,653
You mean, the necklace?

1072
01:06:17,733 --> 01:06:19,620
No, both.

1073
01:06:19,700 --> 01:06:21,566
Both the necklace,
and you, Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

1074
01:06:51,500 --> 01:06:53,400
I guess you like it?

1075
01:06:54,333 --> 01:06:56,653
Yes, the more I look at it,
the more I like it.

1076
01:06:56,733 --> 01:06:58,353
Thank you so much, Mr. Kwon.

1077
01:06:58,433 --> 01:07:01,220
I'm glad it makes you that happy,

1078
01:07:01,300 --> 01:07:02,366
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

1079
01:07:03,833 --> 01:07:06,933
Oh, I wanted to ask you something.

1080
01:07:08,166 --> 01:07:11,386
Why do you keep on
calling me Oh Jin-sim?

1081
01:07:11,466 --> 01:07:13,786
I corrected you many times
that it's Oh Yoon-seo.

1082
01:07:13,866 --> 01:07:16,820
At first, I thought that because that
name is a pseudonym for

1083
01:07:16,900 --> 01:07:19,153
when you're acting,
you should use your

1084
01:07:19,233 --> 01:07:23,720
real name in the office,
since you're here to work.

1085
01:07:23,800 --> 01:07:25,053
But when I look back,

1086
01:07:25,133 --> 01:07:27,786
I'm actually glad I started
calling you by that name.

1087
01:07:27,866 --> 01:07:30,520
- What?
- Because it's just me

1088
01:07:30,600 --> 01:07:31,900
who calls you by that name, right?

1089
01:07:34,500 --> 01:07:37,953
Alright, if it's for that reason,
I'm happy with that.

1090
01:07:38,033 --> 01:07:39,586
Because it's just you, Mr. Kwon,

1091
01:07:39,666 --> 01:07:41,453
who calls me by that name.

1092
01:07:41,533 --> 01:07:44,920
Which means whenever I hear
someone call out Oh Jin-sim,

1093
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:47,400
I know it's you right away.

1094
01:08:01,300 --> 01:08:06,700
By the way, I think that
black car has been following us.

1095
01:08:09,900 --> 01:08:11,000
Or is it just my delusion?

1096
01:08:35,600 --> 01:08:36,633
Oh what?

1097
01:08:37,000 --> 01:08:38,833
Are they really following us?

1098
01:09:13,200 --> 01:09:14,766
Are you alright, Ms. Oh Jin-sim?

1099
01:09:36,866 --> 01:09:38,433
Don't get out, Mr. Kwon.

1100
01:09:54,766 --> 01:09:55,800
What is it?

